<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<section xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"
    xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
    xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" version="5.0"
    xml:id="install_openstack_nova_cli">
    <title>Install OpenStack nova CLI</title>
    <para>This example walks through installing the nova client.
        Before you use a command-line client, you must configure
        environment variables for authentication. </para>
    <procedure>
        <title>To install the nova client:</title>
        <step>
            <title>Install Python</title>
            <para>Install Python 2.6 or later. Currently, the nova
                client does not support Python 3. </para>
        </step>
        <step>
            <title>Install the nova client package</title>
            <para>Choose one of the following methods to install the
                nova client package. <itemizedlist>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><emphasis role="bold">Recommended
                                method:</emphasis>
                            <command>pip</command></para>
                        <para>Install <command>pip</command> through
                            the package manager for your
                                system:<informaltable rules="all">
                                <col width="20%"/>
                                <col width="80%"/>
                                <thead>
                                   <tr>
                                   <th>System</th>
                                   <th>Command</th>
                                   </tr>
                                </thead>
                                <tbody>
                                   <tr>
                                   <td>Mac OS X</td>
                                   <td>
                                   <programlisting language="bash" role="gutter: false"><prompt>$</prompt> sudo easy_install pip</programlisting>
                                   </td>
                                   </tr>
                                   <tr>
                                   <td>Ubuntu 11.10 and earlier</td>
                                   <td>
                                   <programlisting language="bash" role="gutter: false"><prompt>$</prompt> aptitude install python-pip </programlisting>
                                   </td>
                                   </tr>
                                   <tr>
                                   <td>Ubuntu 12.04</td>
                                   <td>
                                   <para>There is a packaged version
                                   so you can use dpkg or aptitude to
                                   install python-novaclient.</para>
                                   <programlisting language="bash" role="gutter: false"><prompt>$</prompt> aptitude install python-novaclient </programlisting>
                                   </td>
                                   </tr>
                                   <tr>
                                   <td>RHEL, CentOS, or Fedora:</td>
                                   <td>
                                   <programlisting language="bash" role="gutter: false"><prompt>$</prompt> yum install python-pip</programlisting>
                                   </td>
                                   </tr>
                                   <tr>
                                   <td>openSUSE 12.2 and earlier:</td>
                                   <td>
                                     <para>There is a <link xlink:href="https://build.opensuse.org/package/show?package=python-novaclient&amp;project=Cloud:OpenStack:Master">packaged version available in the Open Build Service</link> so you can use rpm or zypper to install python-novaclient. Alternatively, you can still use pip.</para>
                                     <programlisting language="bash" role="gutter: false"><prompt>$</prompt> zypper install python-pip</programlisting>
                                   </td>
                                   </tr>
                                   <tr>
                                   <td>openSUSE 12.3:</td>
                                   <td>
                                     <para>There is a packaged version so you can use rpm or zypper to install python-novaclient.</para>
                                     <programlisting language="bash" role="gutter: false"><prompt>$</prompt> zypper install python-novaclient</programlisting>
                                   </td>
                                   </tr>
                                </tbody>
                            </informaltable></para>
                        <para>Run the following command to install the
                            nova client package:
                            <programlisting language="bash" role="gutter: false"><prompt>$</prompt> sudo pip install python-novaclient</programlisting></para>
                        <note>
                            <para>Version values of python-novaclient
                                on the Ubuntu distribution are
                                different from the services versions,
                                such as 2.6.10 instead of
                                2012.1.</para>
                        </note>
                    </listitem>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><emphasis role="bold"
                                >easy_install</emphasis></para>
                        <para>Run the following command to install the
                            nova client package: </para>
                        <programlisting language="bash" role="gutter: false"><prompt>$</prompt> sudo easy_install python-novaclient</programlisting>
                    </listitem>
                </itemizedlist></para>
        </step>
        <step>
            <title>Test the nova client</title>
            <para>To verify that you can talk to the API server, run
                the following commands: </para>
            <programlisting language="bash" role="gutter: false"><prompt>$</prompt> nova credentials</programlisting>
            <programlisting language="bash" role="gutter: false"><prompt>$</prompt> nova image-list </programlisting>
            <para>The first command authenticates, and the second
                command returns a list of images.</para>
        </step>
    </procedure>
</section>


    

